  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "In this WordPress era, why do people still study coding instead of just using it?",
  "response": "Studying coding has several benefits that extend beyond simply using pre-built tools or platforms like WordPress. Here are some reasons why people still opt to learn coding:\n\n1. **Customization**: While platforms like WordPress offer various themes and plugins, knowing how to code allows for greater customization. Coders can create unique features, tailor designs, or optimize functionalities that are not possible with out-of-the-box solutions.\n\n2. **Problem-Solving**: Understanding coding principles means that when issues arise\u2014be it a bug or a performance bottleneck\u2014coders can troubleshoot and solve problems more effectively, rather than relying solely on support forums or external help.\n\n3. **Efficiency**: Knowing how to code can streamline workflows. Developers can automate repetitive tasks, create custom scripts, and optimize existing tools to better fit their needs.\n\n4. **Better Understanding**: Learning to code fosters a deeper understanding of how software and websites work. This knowledge can greatly enhance a person's ability to use various tools effectively and intelligently.\n\n5. **Career Opportunities**: The demand for coding skills continues to grow in various industries. Knowing how to code can open doors to diverse job opportunities in software development, web design, data analysis, and more.\n\n6. **Staying Ahead of Trends**: With the rapid evolution of technology, being proficient in coding allows individuals to keep up with trends and advancements, making them more adaptable in a fast-changing landscape.\n\n7. **Creative Expression**: Coding can be a form of artistic expression. Many developers enjoy creating and manipulating digital experiences, whether through games, web applications, or interactive art.\n\n8. **Community and Collaboration**: The tech community is large and collaborative. Learning to code allows one to contribute to open-source projects, learn from others, and participate in hackathons, enhancing networking opportunities.\n\n9. **Foundational Skills**: Many modern technologies and platforms benefit from coding knowledge. Understanding coding provides foundational skills that are applicable in various areas of technology, including data science, machine learning, and cybersecurity.\n\n10. **Empowerment**: Finally, coding can be empowering. It enables individuals to turn their ideas into reality, allowing entrepreneurs to build their startups or creators to develop applications that reflect their visions.\n\nIn summary, while platforms like WordPress make web development more accessible, there remains significant value in learning to code. It enhances one\u2019s capabilities, fosters creativity, and opens up numerous professional pathways.",
